             Definicon Systems Product Comment Form
                    DSI-32 Coprocessor Board


Definicon  Systems,  Inc.  is very interested in knowing what you 
think about our products.   We have furnished this form for  your 
comments  (both  good  and  bad)  about  the  DSI-32  Coprocessor 
product.   Definicon  will try to respond to questions as soon as 
is possible.  Suggestions and questions received by Definicon may 
be  used  or  distributed by Definicon in any  form  it  believes 
appropriate without any obligation to the originator.   This does 
not  limit  your use of information you originate and  supply  to 
Definicon, however.

In  addition  to  this  form,  a bulletin  board  has  been  made 
available as a focal point for questions,  comments and access to 
Public  Domain software through Trevor Marshall's  Thousand  Oaks 
Technical Database.  If you have a modem attached to your system, 
the  database  may be reached via the public  access  number, (24 
hours a day,  1200 baud) at (805) 492-5472.   Upon accessing  the 
system,  run  the  bulletin board and leave  your  comments.   No 
guarantee  is made about responses to bulletin  board  questions.  
For  uploads of Public Domain software,  the restricted (SYSOP's) 
number (805) 493-1495 may be used.

